NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, burglary.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismis and read in count 2, criminal damage to property.  Motion granted.
The Court comments and sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison systems for a total of five (5) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for thirty-six (36) months.
The court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse program.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Submit to DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
5) Spend six (6) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 10-01-5 by 5:00 p.m.;
6) No contact with the victims or their residences or businesses;
7) Pay court costs;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
10) Pay restitution of $1,134.56 to Mona Hansen d/b/a M&K Quick Stop at 306 S. 4th Avenue, St. Nazianz, WI 54232 and $2,300.00 to Dennis Schnell at PO Box 432, St. Nazianz, WI 54232.  Restitution is to be paid at the rate of $100.00 per month starting 09-01-15.
Minutes.
